OL,3,CFormer UK residents living abroad to
OL,4,Cpay more under pension changes
OL,6,FCurrently, those who leave the UK
OL,7,Fafter at least three years of
OL,8,Fcontributing to their state pension,
OL,9,Foften through National Insurance on
OL,10,Fwages, have to pay #182 annually for a
OL,11,Ftotal of 35 years to qualify for a
OL,12,Ffull rate when they retire.
OL,14,FHowever, from April 2026, state
OL,15,Fpension contributions will rise to
OL,16,F#910 a year, and people will now need
OL,17,Fto live and work in the UK
OL,18,Fcontinuously for 10 years to access
OL,19,Fthe state pension.
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G2/7
